reviews.text: This place was amazing. Was staying at the nearby High Ridge Cabins and saw it was very close by. Tour was about an hour. Tour guide was very friendly and knowledgeable. Plenty of chances for pictures. Nice gift shop. Price went up $2 to $21. But still very worth it. Absolutely beautiful and would recommend to anybody.

Great family fun!!! They have done a great job with their accessibility in the cave and captured the attention of our family from oldest (37) to youngest (1 1/2 yr old). Their use of recessed lighting and the general demeanor of the staff is awesome. The topside attractions are legit as well and you can feel the sense of pride everyone has in their attraction.
Really fun and an interesting experience. More locals should go there. Our guide did a good job handling the young children keeping them safe and in line.

The cave is amazing and our tour guide was very good. The village and Grist Mill are closed this time of year but they are enjoyable as well.  There are also picnic areas and a duck pond. Our family loves visiting Squire Boone Caverns.

Fun place! Was slow because of rainy weather when we visited but still a lot of fun. Our guide was friendly, staff in the shop was a nice woman who was helpful as well. Would recommend this place to others with kids!

Quite gimmicky. They do an excellent job at advertising their farm on social media and bring in droves of people every weekend. They give an impression that the farm is large but the visiting area is reduced to a limited space and you’re sharing it with loads of people. It’s right off the road and offers no educational information. They don’t even go over safety when feeding the Alpacas. Once you’re there you don’t really see a point other than a photo opportunity with nervous animals and of course their barn gift shop. I wish they had a more organized interaction for visitors, but they don’t. It’s a one time thing, if you live close enough.
Knowledgeable friendly staff.  Lots of lovely alpacas and a sweet little gift shop.  Such a fun place!
An informative and inexpensive way to spend a half hour, especially with kids.

Beautiful place for anything you can think to do! We come here every year for family reunions and for our random family days out! Many places to play for kids beautiful lake with many things to do in it! Camping is one thing we haven’t done there yet but plan to very soon!

Buffalo Trace is great park to go visit they have about any thing for anybody. They have  basketball courts, tennis courts, horse shoe pits, several swing sets merry go around, multiple slide sets. Camping which I guess the price is acceptable for being the only one around that area. Fishing is good just have to search for them. They have freebie golf course. A walking path all the way around the lake 1.3 miles around. Swimming is good they have a diving board life gaurds and take breaks for the kids to get out the water and concessions for people to get thing. The host the Pow Wow every year where they have live bands food trucks car show and also a glow run before the fireworks. The only thing I would change is bring some dirt in and fill in low spots where when it rains quit a bit it floods certain areas and makes it difficult to get to parts of the park.

Love it here! There is a large walking trail that encompasses the entire park. There is a playground, lots of picnic areas, and places to explore. We camped in a truck camper in one of the dry camping areas, and we were there just before the start of camping season, so we basically had the park to ourselves. It is definitely worth a visit.
It a great park to go to if you wanna hang out with your friends and just do whatever.
Very nice, little park. Camping looks really nice.

Legit Review.  Legit review I have played there for over 9.75 months now.  I am 41 and a half years old.  Yes there are a bunch of dumb kids there, but there are also many regular adults(like me)that play.  I have NEVER seen a ref shoot at player during a game. Except for that one time but it was a TIMEOUT and that little girl had it comin'!
The staff Mark, Paul, Gosselaar and the owner Steve, aka "The Steve" are always friendly (unless you break a safety rule and then the ref is in his right to shoot you).  Safety first folks! Then teamwork! 
Their prices compare to other paintball fields in the region. The quality may be much less but it's worth it knowing that we dont have to share the field with the "OTHERS"   and as far as using Walmart paint, that stuff will destroy your gun and shoots like a boomerang. We only use K-MART PAINT.   If you own your own equipment STAY HOME cheap skate for better savings.
If you have questions call first. But dont hang up if they dont answer right away. I dont think they know how phones work.   There is often "a" Groupon that can save you a ton of money, but be sure to check out they're website first because the groupon wont give any of the information that you MUST HAVE. 
Overall I always have a great time. I love all the Trump signs hanging on almost everything. There is a really neat Russian helicopter on the farm. I wish it was an USA blackhawkdown helicopter but I'm sure "the Steve" has his reason for it. 
Minus 1 star because I really like frisbee golf and bean bag but we aren't allowed to play those anymore because of cheap hippies.

Steve and staff are great!  We had such a great time with my son's 13th birthday party.  Our ref was really good... very laid back but followed all safety rules to keep the kids safe.  We had a little communication gap in organizing the event but Steve worked hard to make things right... and he did.  More than I can say for most businesses these days.  Way to go guys... looking forward to our next visit.

I visited the Fun Farm as a work outing with Texas Roadhouse and it sure was a treat. Our goal was fun and team building and this was the perfect avenue. The staff was friendly and encouraging despite our beginner level and they matched the courses and games perfectly to our amateur status so we could learn and be challenged without frustration. Their guns are more accurate than Paintball Asylum and overall I had more fun due to the attention and kindness of Fun Farm's main paintball guy (sorry, didn't catch his name). Awesome day and great memories!!!
Kind of small, but a really neat place to visit. A cool piece of American History. I love going to the battlefields.
There was a great historical interpretor who taught us everything there is to know about Corydon!

I went to the Battle Park in CORYDON, IN to see a place of historical factors. .  The young lady from the office was very pleasant and She showed me the cabin.. My pictures show how nice it turned out. I love the area. It was beautiful. And so informative. I recommend Everyone go see it!  A beautiful place to learn some Indiana history and how our forefathers lived.
Pretty but a tree is fallen blocking off the entrance currently.
I love the scene and what they had out

I had called and  had spoke to Maxine Brown. I reserved the school for my friend's Bridal Shower. We booked the space over a month in advance and I mailed the check for the deposit immediately. There were multiple calls from Maxine confirming my date and time which I thought was strange but I excused it. The evening before she had called me and wasn't able to meet with me the next day til 12:30pm instead of 9am. I didn't really have a choice but I told her I would work around her schedule. The day of the event at 10:30am she called and left me a message(I was in church). She was unable to meet me that day and told me that we wouldn't be able to use the venue for the event! I was horrified as I had 30 ladies attending and the event was scheduled to start in 5 hours. Maxine has still not returned my calls or any of my messages. Luckily I was able to use Point Blank Brewery and it all worked out. However, since I ordered items specifically for the Leora Brown School I have to return over half of my items and pay the return shipping and restocking fees. I am an Event Coordinator for the company I work for but I have never dealt with such an unprofessional individual. I highly suggest not using this venue for your events unless you want to scramble a few hours before trying to find another venue.

My thoughts on Culver's; Sashabaw rd. Clarkston, Michigan:
•I really enjoy their cheese curds; made with 'real Wisconsin cheddar'. I love dipping them in their Ranch and Marinara sauces, the flavors boast well together. (Haha, I'm not that serious about it, but still, some wicked good cheese curds dude.) 
•I also love getting the 'North Atlantic Cod Sandwich', I like to get the sandwich without the shredded cheddar; I don't enjoy fish and cheese together in a sandwich- that's just a personal preference not anything to do with the cheese itself, because we all know I love me some cheese. I do however recommend adding pickles to the sandwich and possibly more lettuce,  it seams like I always get a baby sliver. Otherwise, the cod is cooked beautifully and is a beautiful cut of fish that flakes apart wonderfully. 
•Their shakes are 'Handcrafted' and beyond delightful. The last time I went I got the 'Shake of the Day!' 'Caramel Cookie Dough', was just as bewildering and stupefying as it sounds.
5/5 
Cheese curds, on point
